join "Diwata Laya" (Half_mirror) leftmost
[signal arg="laya_start"]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 5/c5s2/Diwata_Laya_appears_and_or_the_first_time_she_looks_at_Principal_B_C_with_recognition.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
"Diwata Laya" appears, and for the first time, she looks at Principal B.C. with recognition.
"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]Ancient and patient. I sense it now.[/color][/i]
"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]You have been teaching for many lifetimes, in many forms.[/color][/i]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 5/c5s2/Principal_B_C_acknowledges_Laya_with_a_respectful_nod.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
Principal B.C. acknowledges Laya with a respectful nod.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Principal: Diwata Laya. I wondered when you would reveal yourself to her.
	Principal: You've been an excellent guide as well.
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]We each teach in our own way. You through observation and patience.[/color][/i]
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]I through connection to truth and spirit.[/color][/i]
	"Celestine (Thinking)": They know each other?
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]Not know. Recognize. Two guides working toward the same purpose.[/color][/i]
else:
	Principal: Diwata Laya. I wondered when you would reveal yourself to him.
	Principal: You've been an excellent guide as well.
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]We each teach in our own way. You through observation and patience.[/color][/i]
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]I through connection to truth and spirit.[/color][/i]
	"Conrad (Thinking)": They know each other?
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]Not know. Recognize. Two guides working toward the same purpose.[/color][/i]
[signal arg="laya_end"]
leave "Diwata Laya"
Mark: Okay, that was cryptic. But I'm more confused about something else.
Mark: Principal, you've been here the whole time. You dealt with each incident officially.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Mark: But you were also leaving cards, watching sis solve them. Why the dual role?
	Principal: Because both roles were necessary.
	Principal: As Principal, I had to ensure justice was served, students were protected, consequences were fair.
	Principal: As B.C., I could guide Celestine to understand the deeper lessons beneath each case.
	Principal: One role handles the immediate situation. The other plants seeds for long-term growth.
	Celestine: How long have you been doing this? Leaving cards, teaching through observation?
	Principal: Many years. Since before you arrived at this school.
	Principal: I've guided other students in different ways. Each person needs different lessons.
	Principal: You, Celestine, needed to learn how to see beneath the surface.
	Principal: To understand that solving a mystery isn't just about finding the culprit.
	Principal: It's about understanding why they made those choices, and what everyone can learn from them.
	Celestine: The cards always appeared after I solved a case, never before.
	Celestine: You wanted me to reach my own conclusions first.
	Principal: Yes. Because if I told you the answers, you would learn nothing.
	Principal: Discovery is the heart of real education.
	leave Principal
	leave Mark
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 5/c5s2/The_protagonist_stands_pacing_thoughtfully.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Celestine stands, pacing thoughtfully.
	Celestine: So each case... each lesson...
	Celestine: They were all building toward something. Training me for something.
else:
