	Principal: Because both roles were necessary.
	Principal: As Principal, I had to ensure justice was served, students were protected, consequences were fair.
	Principal: As B.C., I could guide Conrad to understand the deeper lessons beneath each case.
	Principal: One role handles the immediate situation. The other plants seeds for long-term growth.
	Conrad: How long have you been doing this? Leaving cards, teaching through observation?
	Principal: Many years. Since before you arrived at this school.
	Principal: I've guided other students in different ways. Each person needs different lessons.
	Principal: You, Conrad, needed to learn how to see beneath the surface.
	Principal: To understand that solving a mystery isn't just about finding the culprit.
	Principal: It's about understanding why they made those choices, and what everyone can learn from them.
	Conrad: The cards always appeared after I solved a case, never before.
	Conrad: You wanted me to reach my own conclusions first.
	Principal: Yes. Because if I told you the answers, you would learn nothing.
	Principal: Discovery is the heart of real education.
	leave Principal
	leave Mark
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 5/c5s2/The_protagonist_stands_pacing_thoughtfully.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Conrad stands, pacing thoughtfully.
	Conrad: So each case... each lesson...
	Conrad: They were all building toward something. Training me for something.
join Principal (Principal_half) right
Principal: They were. But not for what you might think.
Principal: Come. There's one more thing you need to understand.
join "Diwata Laya" (Half_mirror) center
[signal arg="laya_start"]
"Diwata Laya": Before the final lesson, prove your readiness once more.
if {selected_subject} == "english":
	[signal arg="start_minigame observation_teaching"]
elif {selected_subject} == "math":
	if {selected_character} == "celestine":
		Celestine: B.C.'s teaching philosophy... it's built on three mathematical principles.
		Celestine: Observation, guidance, and reflection. Each using different reasoning.
	else:
		Conrad: B.C.'s teaching philosophy... it's built on three mathematical principles.
		Conrad: Observation, guidance, and reflection. Each using different reasoning.
	[signal arg="start_minigame logic_grid_teaching_principles_math"]
elif {selected_subject} == "science":
	if {selected_character} == "celestine":
		Celestine: B.C.'s teaching philosophy... it's like how light behaves!
		Celestine: Observation is absorption, guidance is refraction, reflection is... reflection.
		Celestine: Each principle mirrors a different light phenomenon!
	else:
		Conrad: B.C.'s teaching philosophy... it's like how light behaves!
		Conrad: Observation is absorption, guidance is refraction, reflection is... reflection.
		Conrad: Each principle mirrors a different light phenomenon!
	[signal arg="start_minigame logic_grid_teaching_principles_science"]
"Diwata Laya": Good. Your journey nears completion.
[signal arg="laya_end"]
leave "Diwata Laya"
Principal: The final lesson.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	leave Celestine
else:
	leave Conrad
leave Principal
